snippet.textDisplay:
laali mere laal ki jit dekhoon tit laal - Everywhere I turn, I see the brilliant Colour of my beloved (Juela laal)
main ho gayi aap hi laal - I became myself Laal (Red)
Lagi Bina "Joined Without (She)"
Rain Nah Jaage "Leave, don't Awake" (One who hasn't experienced/Awoken to Relationship or Love before)
oho jaage jis noon aap jagaawe - The One Who Should Awake to Love is the One You Awake (Juela laal or Shiva or Bullha Shah)
Phela phar har koi Jaage - Everbody should Awake to the First Love.
par dooga nah jasge koi - Nobody should Awake to the Second Love. As you'll be Saddened by the First break up.
(He) Chal mela noon challiye - Come lets go to the Music Festival.
Aakhir jaana mar ve - In the end ultimately we're gonna die.
pahla Mela Allah keta - This First Meeting Almighty God in the Heavens has done. Nobody should Awake to Second Love.
The Angels have shot their Arrows of Love.
(She) Dukkhi Jaage dukh de karan - Saddness Awake, ones who do saddness.
par Sukkhiya nah jaage koi - However, Happiness nobody Awakes
Lagi Bina "Joined Without (She)"
Rain Nah Jaage "Leave, don't Awake"
(He) Bullha peer manaawe - (Bullha - Another word for God or Shiva or Juela Laal) - Make Bullha your Guide and "Yaar"(Beloved).
(She) Yaar - "Beloved" ho Allah "O God" - (O God You're my Beloved -Shiva or Juela laal)

Jai Hind, Long live Hind, Laal Kaladar, Shahbaz Kalandar!
